## Why JANG?

JANG uses mixed-precision quantization that gives each tensor class the bits it needs — attention stays at 6-8 bits while expert MLPs compress to 2-4 bits — so the model stays coherent at drastically smaller sizes.

See [FORMAT.md](https://github.com/jjang-ai/jangq/blob/main/FORMAT.md) for the format spec.

